# TierList

## Summary
The `TierList` spec is a card that allows users to create and manage a tier-based ranking system. It provides a visual interface for dragging and dropping items into different tiers, as well as tools for customizing the tiers themselves.

## Import
```javascript
import { TierList } from '../tier-list';
```

## Usage as a Field
The `TierList` spec can be used as a field within a consuming card or field. Here's an example:

```json
{
  "type": "card",
  "id": "my-tier-list-card",
  "attributes": {
    "title": "My Tier List",
    "template": { "type": "tier-template", "id": "my-tier-template" },
    "tiers": [],
    "placements": []
  },
  "relationships": {
    "fields": {
      "data": [
        { "type": "field", "id": "tier-list" }
      ]
    }
  }
}
```

```json
{
  "type": "field",
  "id": "tier-list",
  "attributes": {
    "fieldType": "TierList"
  }
}
```

In this example, the `TierList` spec is used as a field within a card. The card has a `template` relationship that links to a `TierTemplate` card, which provides the items to be ranked. The `tiers` and `placements` fields store the current state of the tier list.

## Template Usage
To use the `TierList` spec in a template, you can simply reference the `@fields.` prefix, like this:

```handlebars
<@fields.tier-list />
```

This will render the tier list UI, allowing users to drag and drop items into the different tiers.
